@Caro

Not a golfer or a golf fan, but I'd imagine that there's no need for such a term in golf.  Tee shots are by their very nature all hit high and long (assuming proficiency); putts are just the opposite.

In baseball, on the other hand, the batter is not hitting a stationary ball on a tee; he's hitting one coming at him at 100 mph that may curve in any direction--or not.  What happens when a batter swings is unpredictable and often not what the batter intended.  And all possible outcomes can occur at any time:  pop flies, long drives into the gap, line drives to infielders, ground balls, foul balls, and nothing at all (swinging strikes).

